{"questionId":"9076863","questionHtml":"<p>A mass <em>m</em> attached to a string of length <em>R</em> moves in a vertical circle with a constant speed.&nbsp;The tension in the string at the top of the circle is <em>T</em>. What is the kinetic energy of the mass at&nbsp;the top of the circle?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{R\\left( {T + mg} \\right)}}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mi>g</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{R\\left( {T - mg} \\right)}}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mi>g</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{Rmg}}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{R\\left( {2T + mg} \\right)}}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>m</mi>\n          <mi>g</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076863","referenceCode":"18N.1.HL.TZ0.5","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A mass m attached to a string of length R moves in a vertical circle with a constant speed. The tension in the string at the top of the circle is T. What is the kinetic energy of t","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.1 – Circular motion","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.2 – Forces","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.3 – Work, energy, and power","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}